		A peaceful and compromising solution		
	</tr>
	
	
		<tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA">
			<td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%">
			<a href="/user.asp?usr=26557" class="AuthorLink">NytCrie_needs_ign_merge$$$</a>&nbsp;<br> 
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 5<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> May 00<br>
			</span>
			
			
			
			</td>
			
			
			<td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span> 
			5/26/00 2:48pm 
			<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> A peaceful and compromising solution			
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				this message has been posted elsewhere as well, feel free to spread it to your personal guild boards. <br>  <br> This is a proposition to try to end the bickering, please donnot flame as I do not make accusations.okay, time for my 100pp worth ( I like to give myself an ego boost now in then, good for the soul; that and I get long winded sometimes ) <br>  <br> This is going to be posted on as many message boards as I can find to post it on, and I hope other people will feel free to cross post it on any boards I miss for me to spread the word. <br>  <br> Okay, for some reason, almost every idea propsed to try to make this server a more civil place to play has been shot down by one of any number of factions with any number of reasons. <br>  <br> 1----FIrst complaint I would like to address: surfing message boards.  Given that the calander was originally planned as a message board...it would be ONE message board, and would take you perhaps 10 minutes to look it over.  The only other seemingly feasible idea (which I will detail later in this post) would require much more time and effort. <br>  <br> 2)----THen we have those opposed to the mailing list based calandar.  Are you saying you don't check your email daily? weekly?  I would be one lost puppy without mine, I can guarantee it as it is the most efficient method of communication between my multinational friends (and yes, I now have an IRL friend in Japan, so language will soon no longer be a problem for me). <br>  <br> 3)----We have the people under the impression that it's tough luck if you don't raid Vox the instant she spawns, or whatever dragon/plane there is.  My argument against this is the same as many have presented here.  I work from 6 AM EST to 5 PM EST Monday thru Friday.  I get home aound 5:30 EST, in the shower by 5:45 EST, then eating supper about 6:30 EST.  I check my email and guild board between the shower and supper.  I log onto EQ at 7:00 PM EST.  By the reasoning most Veeshan folks have presented here (sorry, just seems those are the ones presenting this argument) I will NEVER be able to do another dragon, or visit another plane again, as they will be dying at the time I log on.  Guess I may as well not play then, because after time, that will pretty much be the only way I can improve my gear. <br>  <br> 4)----We have guilds not willing to work with each other, and people opposed to it.  I can understand both arguments in the open-guild/guild-only raid department.  Each plan has it's merrits andit's downfalls.  Each plan is up to the guild organizing the raid I believe.  This should NOT be an issue. <br>  <br> 5)----The current assumption that the Japanese will not respect any of these plans anyway, so why not live in total Anarchy is just kinda one-sided in my opinion for one reason: I have not heard this from one single japanese person.  You show me where the Japanese people state they will not cooperate with we Americans (and whatever other nationality we have on this server...god I miss my Swedes and Aussies back on BB) and I will then buy these statements 100%.  Actions may speak louder than words, but I haven't heard anyone try to ask them; perhaps they do it that way because they think we are doing it to them.  Just a thought there folks. <br>  <br> SO, what to do to try to aleviate everyone's complaints and pressures? <br>  <br> We could continue to go as we are now, slamming and bashing, flaming and slandering, and just generally screwing up the whole plan to try to get everyone to get along. <br>  <br> Or, we could manage to unite in one way or another to work out the wrinkles in this new server to make it a lot more pleasant than it currently is.  I know that if all the bickering and bitching doesn't stop soon, I am likely to cancel my account as I don't pay my monthly fee to have stress added to my life, I get enough of that from family and work.  I'm sure others feel the same, and other still think we all are reacting a bit rashly. <br>  <br> With all that said, please allow me to make a proposition or two. <br>  <br> First, and likely the one involving more work on the individual basis, is that in order to not step on each others toes, we put the links to every guild's message boards here, so that others may browse about to see if another guild is planning a raid the same time you are.  Now personally, this should be the leaders responsibility, since being a leader in any other aspect of any other game I've played involves a bit more work to make a successful guild and have healthy relations with other people.  Trust me, been ddown the road many times in other games, and considered it here.  Yes this means countless hours staring at your web rowser of choice while posting, reading extensive threads in various message boards, and watching your password compilation become equal in size to the MP3s you've been downloading. <br>  <br> SOunds liek a lot of work, but it would seemingly keep everyone happy. <br>  <br> There is a simpler way though, and for you people touting you want an in-game way of doing it, and this is it: we form a Guild Council. <br>  <br> Before you start with the groaning and rolling of eyes (or laughing and falling out of chairs) please hear me out. <br>  <br> Every guild on the server assigns one of their officers the title of Ambassador, Senator (although everyone would automaitcly think you a ninja looter and yer banging yer woodelf intern), Councelour, or whatever fancy title you want meaning the same basic thing.  Once a month on a set day and time (perhaps the first of every month at midnight GMT which would be 7 PM EST for the time zone challenged) these Ambassadors would meet in a specified zone that is low in population or step into a designated chatroom to have a meeting.  SOme rules would have to be made for conducting the meetings (have a &quot;chairman&quot; to keep the room in order, queueing of questions, etc) so they are not utter chaos.  At that meeting, the ambassodors discuss the current state of affairs on Saryrn, scheduling of raids to keep each other happy, perhaps diplomaticly resolve inter-guild conflicts, etc. all in a diplomatic fashion.  Things would be voted on.  If we truly felt it necessary, perhaps problem guilds or such could effectively be ignored or shunned by others, not in a harrassing manner mind you, or whatever was deemed appropriate by the Council.  All guilds involved would agree to abide by the decisions of the council and so on.  Yes, it's a little ploitical, but a little politics are involved no matter what you try to do in life (even if it is simulated).  To ease things, perhaps Ambassadors could be voted into various functions for the Council (chairman/speaker, secretary/records keeper, stuff like that).  We could get one of the more Web-inclined to design a site if that would be preferable where we could meet there. <br>  <br> I think this proposal is fair enough that it could be done entirely from within the game, and it would be a good way for all guilds to relate with one another, be they warring or allies or indifferent to one another.  It would require some effort from EVERYONE, not just the people coming from BB or Veeshann.  One thing we all have to agree on is that this server is NOT BB or Veesh, so we must try to come to a way of doing things on our own.  I think this is an excellent idea, as it covers a little of what the biggest complaints are. <br>  <br> As such, I would like it if we could have each guild at least appoint a representative to meet and discuss the possibility of setting this up. <br>  <br> As an officer of Familjen, I would be more than honored to represent our guild as it's Ambassador if they would have me. <br>  <br> Let's all please take a step to try and owrk together, not so much in terms of raids, but as a community because like it or not, we are stuck here with each other.  I know I would much rather get along than to be at each others throats. <br>  <br> Feel free to respond to me in E-mail about this should you desire to do so, but I do ask we give this a shot, and this message is cross posted as much as possible. <br>  <br> thank you <br>  <br> Kiriani Greywynd <br> Familjen--Saryrn <br> nytcrie@lenzlink.net <br>  <br> 		

			</td>
		</tr>
