			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Okay, I have an answer to the constant retort of &quot;there was no problem till people vcame up with solutions&quot;. <br>  <br> There is no problem IN YOUR OPINION because you are among those who CAN be on early enough to play Race for the Raids. <br>  <br> The main reason many of us feel *some* form of organization could be used is to help AVOID future conflicts and flaming such as this. <br>  <br> The Council Idea is so that we could, as a server, settle arguments such as these once and for all, with everyone agreeing on the decisions the council comes to. <br>  <br> It would end the useless bickering and flaming. <br>  <br> As for asking myself the same question about change:  I am more than willing to, and often I have.  You show me where the way of chaos is any better than what we propose and I'll change to your way.  SHow me how it benefits me and all the other people who don't have the ability to be on when the servers come up and race everyone to a raid and I'll do it your way.  I have changed the way I did things already on this server.  I am open to change, and truthfully, I am hoping for change from the way things are now.		

